Work From Hope captures the moment a lot of us find ourselves in – working from home and hoping everyone is safe, while key workers continue their vital work. The Guardian’s deputy creative director, Chris Clarke, took inspiration from the familiar phrase, hoping to reframe it in a more positive light. “It feels a wonderfully positive thing to do in solidarity during this remarkably difficult time.” It is printed on 100% sustainable bamboo paper and available in two sizes, A5 & A3. Seventy per cent of the Guardian’s profits will be paid to NHS charities. Buy your exclusive print here Price£25 (A5) and £55 (A3), including free delivery Prints Prints are available in two sizes, A5 & A3 (148 x 210mm & 297 x 420mm) on museum-grade, fine-art paper stocks, with archival standards guaranteeing quality for 100+ years. All editions are printed and quality-checked by experts at theprintspace, the UK’s leading photo and fine-art print provider. DeliveryArtworks are delivered to your door, unframed. theprintspace takes great care in packaging your artwork, with a no-quibble satisfaction guarantee should you be unhappy in any way. Global shipping is available. ContactEmail: guardianprintsales@theprintspace.co.uk